        int n = nums1.length;
        if (n == 0) return true;

        // We need to check if we can make all elements even OR if we can make all elements odd.

        // Helper function to check if a target parity (0 for even, 1 for odd) is achievable.
        // This function tries to find a choice for each nums2[i] such that nums2[i] % 2 == targetParity.
        //
        // For each i, we must satisfy:
        // 1. nums2[i] = nums1[i] AND nums1[i] % 2 == targetParity
        // OR
        // 2. nums2[i] = nums1[i] - nums1[j] (j != i, nums1[i] - nums1[j] >= 1) AND (nums1[i] - nums1[j]) % 2 == targetParity

        // The parity of nums1[i] - nums1[j] is (nums1[i] % 2 - nums1[j] % 2 + 2) % 2.
        // Let P_i = nums1[i] % 2 and P_j = nums1[j] % 2.
        // Parity of difference is (P_i - P_j + 2) % 2.

        // If targetParity is 0 (Even):
        // - Option 1: P_i = 0
        // - Option 2: P_i - P_j = 0 (mod 2) => P_i = P_j
        //
        // If targetParity is 1 (Odd):
